HEADWORD: Birds-mouth
<hw>Bird's-mouth`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>An interior angle or notch cut across a piece of timber, for the
reception of the edge of another, as that in a rafter to be laid on a
plate; -- commonly called <altname>crow's-foot</altname> in the United
States.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

